## Implementation Structure

### New Helper Functions

Add to `plink_common.hpp/cpp`:

```cpp
//! Check if a path refers to a native PLINK format file
bool IsNativePlinkFormat(const string &path);

//! Load variant metadata from any DuckDB-readable source.
//! Executes context.Query(), maps columns by name (case-insensitive)
//! falling back to positional, synthesizes a pvar-format text buffer,
//! and returns a standard VariantMetadataIndex.
VariantMetadataIndex LoadVariantMetadataFromSource(ClientContext &context,
                                                    const string &source);

//! Load sample info from any DuckDB-readable source.
//! Same approach: query, map columns, synthesize psam-format buffer,
//! return standard SampleInfo.
SampleInfo LoadSampleInfoFromSource(ClientContext &context,
                                     const string &source);
```

Add to `pfile_reader.cpp`:

```cpp
//! Load full sample metadata from a non-native source for
//! genotype/sample orient modes. Returns PfileSampleMetadata with all
//! columns preserved.
PfileSampleMetadata LoadPfileSampleMetadataFromSource(
    ClientContext &context, const string &source, SampleInfo &sample_info_out);
```

### Dispatch Logic

Replace direct parser calls with format-aware dispatch:

```cpp
// Before (in bind functions):
bind_data->variants = LoadVariantMetadataIndex(context, pvar_path);

// After:
if (IsNativePlinkFormat(pvar_path)) {
    bind_data->variants = LoadVariantMetadataIndex(context, pvar_path);
} else {
    bind_data->variants = LoadVariantMetadataFromSource(context, pvar_path);
}
```

This pattern applies at every companion file loading site. Since
`LoadVariantMetadataIndex` and `LoadSampleInfo` are the shared entry
points called by all functions (read_pgen, read_pfile, and all P2
utility functions), adding the dispatch at these call sites covers the
entire codebase.

An alternative is to add the dispatch inside `LoadVariantMetadataIndex`
and `LoadSampleInfo` themselves (detect format, delegate). This is
cleaner but changes the existing function signatures to require
`ClientContext` where they currently only take a path. The preferred
approach depends on how many call sites exist — if most already have
context available, internalize the dispatch.

### Bind Restructuring for `read_pvar` / `read_psam`

Currently `PvarBind` and `PsamBind` pass the first positional argument
directly to `ReadFileLines(context, path)`, which calls
`FileSystem::OpenFile`. If the source is a table name or non-native file,
this fails before any format detection can run.

The fix: add format detection before the file read:

```cpp
// In PvarBind:
auto source = input.inputs[0].GetValue<string>();
if (IsNativePlinkFormat(source)) {
    // Existing path: ReadFileLines → parse header → build schema
    auto lines = ReadFileLines(context, source);
    // ... existing bind logic
} else {
    // New path: query source, map columns, emit result
    auto result = QueryExternalSource(context, source);
    // ... build schema from result columns
}
```

For `read_pvar` and `read_psam`, the non-native path is different from
the companion file loading path: instead of building a
`VariantMetadataIndex`, these functions need to emit the data as a table
scan. The implementation should materialize the query result and emit
rows from it during scan, using the same column mapping logic.

